  "market_context": "Price had formed a strong bearish momentum candle indicating aggressive supply; analyst identified the zone and projected it forward expecting future supply reaction.",
  "key_observation": "Price briefly pushed above the aggressive supply zone (failure test/false breakout), then reversed sharply downward, confirming the supply zone's validity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified an aggressive supply zone based on a large red momentum candle that engulfed prior candles.",
    "Step 2: Analyst dragged the supply zone horizontally to the right as a projected future resistance area.",
    "Step 3: Price approached the projected supply zone, made a tiny false breakout above it (failure test), then collapsed sharply downward.",
    "Step 4: After the crash, analyst drew a new aggressive supply zone to the right based on the fresh supply activity, and observed a second failure test with wicks followed by another downside crash."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Aggressive supply zones often trigger failure tests (false breakouts) before strong rejection; after a confirmed supply reaction, a new supply zone can be projected forward for subsequent entries.",
